    <note type="dates"><date>1838–1935</date></note>
    <sex value="M"/>
    <note type="biography">
        <p>Irish-born gardener and writer. Under-gardener at the Royal Botanic Society, Regent’s Park, 1861–3; foreman of the herbaceous department, 1863–7. Travelled in France, 1867–8, and North America, 1870. Promoted the use of perennials. Founded the <hi rend="italic">Garden</hi>, 1871, and <hi rend="italic">Gardening Illustrated</hi>, 1879.</p></note>
